## 8. Creative Commons Attributions

### FIRST Information Exchange Policy (IEP) 2.0 Framework Definition

- **Copyright:** Copyright © 2019 Forum of Incident Response and Security Teams, Inc. (FIRST). All Rights Reserved.
- **License:** Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike (CC-BY-SA)
- **Source:** https://www.first.org/iep
- **JSON Specification:** https://www.first.org/iep/2.0/first-iep-2.0-json-specification.pdf
- **Use in ThreatRecall API:** IEP 2.0 policies are first-class nodes in the knowledge graph. The /api/v1/iep-policies endpoints expose IEP policy management and IEP-filtered retrieval. HASL fields (Handling, Action, Sharing, Licensing) govern threat intelligence sharing restrictions at the data layer.
- **Share-Alike Scope:** Per CC-BY-SA, the IEP 2.0 derived schema definitions within ThreatRecall (specifically, the JSON schema structures implementing the 12 mandatory IEP 2.0 fields) are available under CC-BY-SA. This share-alike obligation does not extend to the API layer, authentication system, tenant isolation logic, routing, middleware, SDK, or any other proprietary component.
- **IEP Co-chairs at time of release:** Terry MacDonald, Paul McKitrick, Merike Kaeo

